docs/combat_authority_map.md:67:Current finding: the seam is intentionally narrow. It proves `RON custom signals -> per-Digimon blueprint Rust module -> generic kernel hooks -> canonical state/events/snapshots` for the Patamon Holy Support Grace case. It does not move all move sets, beats, targeting rules, or mechanic ownership into per-Digimon modules. Shared combat systems should stay branch-light while later slices expand the blueprint layer deliberately.
docs/combat_authority_map.md:89:`src/bin/combat_cli.rs` consumes shared combat surfaces directly. It builds snapshots through `build_snapshot_from_ecs_with_sp`, asks the legality/query layer via `query_action_affordance`, writes `ActionIntent`, and reads `CombatEvent` messages for logging and dashboard output.
docs/combat_authority_map.md:97:| R092 | The audit map identifies the current single-source-of-truth split across data, custom-signal intent, live action, blueprint dispatch, kernel transitions, mechanic hooks, validation snapshots, and CLI consumers. | `src/data/skills_ron.rs`, `src/data/units_ron.rs`, `src/combat/turn_system/mod.rs`, `src/combat/turn_system/pipeline.rs`, `src/combat/blueprints/mod.rs`, `src/combat/kernel.rs`, `src/combat/observability.rs`, `src/bin/combat_cli.rs` | Covered as a current-state audit |
docs/combat_authority_map.md:102:| R098 | The CLI uses shared action-query and snapshot surfaces, but full CLI/runtime smoke proof remains downstream work. | `src/bin/combat_cli.rs`, `src/combat/action_query.rs`, `src/combat/observability.rs`, `docs/m015_failure_ledger.md` | Covered with a qualified current-state finding |
docs/combat_authority_map.md:108:- The seeded blueprint seam should expand by adding per-Digimon modules and typed signals, not by adding per-character branches inside shared combat systems.
docs/combat_authority_map.md:112:The current source of truth is split across declarative data (`src/data/skills_ron.rs`, `src/data/units_ron.rs`), shared runtime action processing (`src/combat/turn_system/mod.rs`, `src/combat/turn_system/pipeline.rs`, `src/combat/resolution.rs`), seeded per-Digimon blueprint dispatch (`src/combat/blueprints/mod.rs`, `src/combat/blueprints/patamon.rs`), shared kernel transitions (`src/combat/kernel.rs`), shared mechanic hooks (`src/combat/twin_core.rs`, `src/combat/battery_loop.rs`, `src/combat/holy_support.rs`, `src/combat/predator_loop.rs`, `src/combat/precision_mind_game.rs`), observation surfaces (`src/combat/observability.rs`), and CLI consumption (`src/bin/combat_cli.rs`).
